  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 52, 57.305044}", 
    "history" -> {"14.0", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"Bravyi theorem"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiMutualInformation[grn, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the mutual \
information between the subsystem consisting of fermion modes {k1, k2, ...} \
\\[Subset] {1, 2, ..., n} in the Bravyi state characterized by n*n matrix grn \
of single-particle Green's functions. \
BravyiMutualInformation[NambuGreen[{grn, anm}], {k1, k2, ...}] or \
BravyiMutualInformation[{grn, anm}, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the mutual \
information in the Bravyi state characterized by n*n matrices grn and anm of \
normal and anomalous Green's functions, respectively. \
BravyiMutualInformation[state, {k1, k2, ...}] is equivalent to \
BravyiMutualInformation[BravyiGreen[in], {k1, k2, ...}] for Bravyi state. \
BravyiMutualInformation[{k1, k2, ...}] is an operator form of \
BravyiMutualInformation to be applied to Green's functions or Bravyi state.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "BravyiMutualInformation",
     "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "BravyiMutualInformation", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiMutualInformation"}},
